Virtual Environment:
====================
 > virtual environment is isolated python environment that allows
   to manage dependencies for different projects separately.

 > it helps to avoid conflicts between packages required by different project.

 > it allows to maintain different versions of packages for different projects.

 > it provides a clean environment for testing and development.

 Creating a Virtual Environment:
 -------------------------------
 > using venv module (built-in):

 python -m venv name_of_env
  (python -m venv myenv)

